\par Method developed for the chro
matograph to analyze gas samples includes many parameters of the process, such as the specific task time sequences, temperatures in working zones, names and chromatographic parameters of the gas or liquid to be analyzed, calibration standards, alarm level
s for different components, types of detectors installed, parameters of the data acquisition, processing, analyzing, and outputting the results to other electronic equipment. 
\par    The Method for a particular application is set up through several }{\b Method Menu}{ items:
\par }{\b Method|Edit}{ item opens the }{\uldb Method Dialog Box}{\v ID_METHODDIALOG}{ to set the time schedule of the GC operations, Oven and Detector temperatures, points to be analyzed and to enable/disable alarms in those points. 
\par }{\b Method|Detector}{ item opens the }{\uldb Detector Dialog Box}{\v ID_DETECTORDIALOG}{
 so the user can enable/disable the particular detector, select the detector type, select the data acquisition parameters and the peak detection algorithm, and set the 4-20 mA analog output range.
\par }{\b Method|Components}{ item opens the }{\uldb Components Dialog Box}{\v ID_COMPONENTSDIALOG}{ where the user can input the names, retention times, and other chromatographic parameters of the gas or liquid to be analyzed.
\par }{\b Method|Standards}{ item opens the }{\uldb Standards Dialog Box}{\v\uldb ID_STANDARDSDIALOG}{ where the user inputs the concentration of the Standards (up to four) to be used for calibrating the instrument. 
\par }{\b Method|Save}{ item saves all the parameters into the opened JOB file. It is possible to save different Methods into several JOB files; on start of the WPEAK prog
ram, the particular Method can be loaded automatically if one places the corresponding JOB file name into the \'93Load File\'94 edit box in the }{\uldb Preferences Dialog Box}{\v ID_PREFERENCESDIALOG}{ that can be opened with the }{\b Options|Preferences}
{ menu item.       
